  "narrative": "As of April 1, 2026, capital is flowing predominantly into the Energy sector, which has seen a significant increase of +12.7% compared to the SPY, indicating strong investor confidence likely driven by rising oil prices or geopolitical factors. Financials have also attracted some capital with a modest gain of +1.5%, while Technology remains relatively stable with a slight increase of +0.5%. In contrast, sectors like Consumer Discretionary, Communication Services, and Materials are experiencing outflows, with declines of -0.3%, -0.7%, and -0.9%, respectively, suggesting a cautious consumer sentiment amid macroeconomic uncertainties. \n\nThe macroeconomic backdrop shows a declining fed funds rate at 3.64%, which is down 16% year-over-year, potentially easing borrowing costs and supporting the financial sector. However, the increase in the VIX to 24.06 (+11% YoY) indicates rising market volatility, which could be influencing bearish sentiment in options for companies like GOOGL and META. Investors should watch the performance of the Energy sector and monitor macroeconomic indicators, particularly interest rates and volatility, as these will likely impact capital flows moving forward.",
